  "body": "As the logs below show, a remote disconnected shortly after being added to the PeerPool, and although we processed the disconnection request and `Peer._run()` returned, it was not removed from `PeerPool.connected_nodes`\r\n\r\n```\r\n   DEBUG  07-06 15:04:06        peer  Finished P2P handshake with <Node(0x94c1@192.81.208.223)>, using sub-protocol (eth, 63)\r\n[...]\r\n   DEBUG  07-06 15:04:06        peer  Finished (eth, 63) handshake with <Node(0x94c1@192.81.208.223)>\r\n   DEBUG  07-06 15:04:06        peer  Ignoring GetBlockHeaders (cmd_id=19) msg from ETHPeer <Node(0x94c1@192.81.208.223)> as we haven't performed the chain-split check yet\r\n   DEBUG  07-06 15:04:10        peer  Ignoring Transactions (cmd_id=18) msg from ETHPeer <Node(0x94c1@192.81.208.223)> as we haven't performed the chain-split check yet\r\n   DEBUG  07-06 15:04:10        peer  Ignoring Transactions (cmd_id=18) msg from ETHPeer <Node(0x94c1@192.81.208.223)> as we haven't performed the chain-split check yet\r\n    INFO  07-06 15:04:11        peer  Adding peer: ETHPeer <Node(0x94c1@192.81.208.223)>\r\n[...]\r\n   DEBUG  07-06 15:04:13        peer  ETHPeer <Node(0x94c1@192.81.208.223)> disconnected: disconnect_requested\r\n[...]\r\n    INFO  07-06 15:05:05        peer  Connected peers: 0 inbound, 3 outbound\r\n   DEBUG  07-06 15:05:05        peer  == Peer details == \r\n   DEBUG  07-06 15:05:05        peer  ETHPeer <Node(0x94c1@192.81.208.223)>: running=False, subscribers=2, longest_subscriber_queue=0\r\n   DEBUG  07-06 15:05:05        peer  ETHPeer <Node(0xd871@51.15.217.106)>: running=True, subscribers=2, longest_subscriber_queue=0\r\n   DEBUG  07-06 15:05:05        peer  ETHPeer <Node(0xc8b9@178.62.246.6)>: running=True, subscribers=2, longest_subscriber_queue=0\r\n   DEBUG  07-06 15:05:05        peer  == End peer details == \r\n```\r\n",
